olive oil
1 packet brown rice
1 packet fine breadcrumbs
1 packet garlic paste
1 cucumber
1 capsicum
1 tomato
1 drizzle white wine vinegar
1 packet tomato paste
1 tsp brown sugar
1 bag baby spinach leaves
1 packet beef & pork mince
1 sachet Mumbai Spice Blend
0.74 cup water
1 packet Greek-Style Yoghurt

• Half-fill a medium saucepan with water.
Add brown rice and a generous pinch of salt.
• Bring to the boil over high heat and cook,
uncovered, until tender, 25-30 minutes. Drain
rice and return to saucepan.

• Meanwhile, roughly chop capsicum.
• In a medium bowl, combine beef & pork mince,
fine breadcrumbs, 1/2 the garlic paste and a
generous pinch of salt and pepper.
• Using damp hands, roll heaped spoonfuls of
mince mixture into small meatballs (4-5 per
person). Transfer to a plate.

TIP: The garlic paste helps to bind the meatballs!

• In a large frying pan, heat a drizzle of olive oil
over medium-high heat.
• Cook meatballs, turning, until browned and
cooked through, 8-10 minutes (cook in batches
if your pan is getting crowded). Transfer to a
plate.
• Return frying pan to medium-high heat with a
drizzle of olive oil. Cook capsicum until tender,
4-5 minutes. Transfer to a bowl.

TIP: The meatballs will char slightly in the pan, this
adds to the flavour!

• Meanwhile, roughly chop cucumber and
tomato.
• In a second medium bowl, combine cucumber,
tomato and a drizzle of white wine vinegar and
olive oil. Season to taste and set aside.

• Wipe out the frying pan, then return to
medium-low heat with a drizzle of olive oil. Cook
Mumbai spice blend and tomato paste until
fragrant, 1 minute.
• Stir in the water and brown sugar. Remove from
heat, then add meatballs and capsicum and stir
to coat. Season to taste.

• Stir baby spinach leaves through brown rice.
• Divide brown rice between bowls. Top with beef
and pork meatballs.
• Spoon remaining tomato and capsicum sauce
over meatballs.
• Serve with zingy cucumber salsa and dollop with
Greek-style yoghurt. Enjoy!